condition.text: Moderate or heavy rain with thunder

alert.headline: UK Met Office
alert.desc:
Information on update: Warning extended further north across a larger part of southern England and East Anglia, with the  likelihood of impacts increased, and ice included as part of the warning. Warning has also been extended into Thursday, primarily to include residual ice impacts that may persist into the morning travel period. An area of rain, sleet and snow is expected to develop over southwest England during Tuesday evening and move east during early Wednesday before clearing mid-morning. Whilst drier conditions may develop for a time through the middle of the day, a further spell of sleet and snow is likely to develop during the afternoon and move east into the evening. There remains significant uncertainty in how far north snow develops as well as whether accumulations are focused mainly over higher ground. 

At this stage, the focus for the higher snow accumulations is across England south of the M4 during later Wednesday where there is a chance that some places could see 5-10 cm falling in a few hours. Earlier in the day and across the wider warning area, accumulations are expected to be lower, typically 1-3 cm. As snow clears on Wednesday night, clearing skies will result in ice developing on untreated surfaces with impacts lingering into Thursday morning. For further details see https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/weather/warnings-and-advice/uk-warnings
